If obj is a Django lazy object, return it coerced to text;
otherwise return it unchanged.

(Similar to django.utils.encoding.force_text, but doesn't alter non-text objects.)

Response example:
{
  "status": "success",
  "job_id": "1ZymBc-00041N-9X",
  "emails": [
    "user@example.com",
    "email@example.com",
  ],
  "failed_emails": {
    "email1@gmail.com": "temporary_unavailable",
    "bad@address": "invalid",
    "email@example.com": "duplicate",
    "root@example.org": "permanent_unavailable",
    "olduser@example.net": "unsubscribed"
  }
}

Unwraps SparkPost event structure, and returns event_class, event, raw_event

raw_event is of form {'msys': {event_class: {...event...}}}

Can return None, None, raw_event for SparkPost "ping" raw_event={'msys': {}}
